1️⃣ Node Metrics

Metrics Server collects resource usage of each node.

Node metrics:

CPU usage – Total CPU used by all pods on that node

Memory usage – Total memory used by pods on that node

Example command:

kubectl top nodes

Example output:

NAME        CPU(cores)   CPU%   MEMORY(bytes)   MEMORY%
node-1      250m         12%    1024Mi          40%
2️⃣ Pod Metrics

Metrics Server collects resource usage of each pod.

Pod metrics:

CPU usage of pod

Memory usage of pod

Example command:

kubectl top pods

Example output:

NAME             CPU(cores)   MEMORY(bytes)
frontend-pod     50m          120Mi
backend-pod      30m          90Mi
3️⃣ Container Metrics

Each pod can have multiple containers, and metrics are collected per container.

Container metrics:

CPU usage of container

Memory usage of container

Example command:

kubectl top pod <pod-name> --containers

Example output:

POD             CONTAINER        CPU(cores)   MEMORY(bytes)
frontend-pod    nginx-container  40m          100Mi
frontend-pod    sidecar          10m          20Mi


